# Interaction Patterns

## Whip Element Interactions

The whip weapon links to: `https://github.com/sungchun12/claiw`

### Hover Glow Effect

```css
.whip-interactive {
  transition: filter 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  cursor: pointer;
}

.whip-interactive:hover,
.whip-interactive:focus-visible {
  filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px var(--color-accent-glow, #00D4FF)) 
          drop-shadow(0 0 20px var(--color-accent-glow, #00D4FF));
}

.whip-interactive:active {
  filter: drop-shadow(0 0 12px #00D4FF) 
          drop-shadow(0 0 30px #00D4FF);
  transform: scale(0.98);
}
```

### Click Handler Pattern

Always use this pattern for external links:

```tsx
const handleClick = () => {
  window.open('https://github.com/sungchun12/claiw', '_blank', 'noopener,noreferrer');
};
```

Or with native anchor:
```tsx
<a 
  href="https://github.com/sungchun12/claiw"
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"
>
```

## Accessibility Requirements

1. **Keyboard navigation**: All interactive elements must be focusable via Tab
2. **Focus states**: `:focus-visible` must match `:hover` styling
3. **ARIA labels**: Use `aria-label` for non-text interactive elements
4. **Enter/Space**: Both keys should trigger click actions

```tsx
const handleKeyDown = (e: React.KeyboardEvent) => {
  if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
    e.preventDefault();
    handleClick();
  }
};
```

## Interactive Component Template

```tsx
<button
  onClick={handleClick}
  onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}
  className="whip-interactive"
  aria-label="Open claiw project on GitHub"
  tabIndex={0}
>
  {children}
</button>
```

## Animation Options

### CSS-only pulse (simple)
```css
@keyframes glow-pulse {
  0%, 100% { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px #00D4FF); }
  50% { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 16px #00D4FF) drop-shadow(0 0 24px #00D4FF); }
}

.whip-interactive:hover {
  animation: glow-pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
}
```

